Body: Project intro video and story behind it: I knew that eye health professionals (like most of the other health professionals) use social networking on very limited basis, because they work hard for many hours and saving each free moment. You can test it on LinkedIn or Facebook - it's less than 1% of health practitioners around. So we had this ophthalmology conference where I had a presentation on dry eye treatment options and MD ophthalmologist Andrius Ruzgys, President of local society of ophthalmologists - was showing video from one of his surgeries in Scotland, he is ophthalmology surgeon working in both Lithuania and UK, Scotland and frequently traveling in between. Our team was already on EyeGlob.Net concept - directly responding professionals needs. So I "catch him on a go" for a short conversation and feedback about our ideas. We where lucky to get this on "tape". Real ophthalmologist in real life confirming his real demand! This was not paid, agreed or intended to be used as commercial. What could better promote the project?     https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vN7yi7J1e7w&t=8s
